{"_id":"yB4p8yqYIkMbdT8l","name":"Insanity","img":"systems/dnd5e/icons/skills/red_22.jpg","description":" ","results":[{"_id":"NjEyNTg1ZTc0NzE2","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Synesthesia. You can hear colors, smell sounds, or taste textures. Regardless of the specific manifestation, you have disadvantage on all Perception and Investigation skill checks. (1)","img":"https://static.thenounproject.com/png/854690-200.png","resultId":null,"weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"collection":null,"rangeL":1,"rangeH":1},{"_id":"NDgxZDJiOTRkNDJm","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Kleptomania. Once per day when you are in a personal residence or marketplace, the DM can call on you to succeed on a Wisdom saving throw (DC 12) or attempt to steal an item of insignificant practical and monetary value. (2)","img":"https://static.thenounproject.com/png/2481223-200.png","resultId":null,"weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"collection":null,"rangeL":2,"rangeH":2},{"_id":"MjUyYmI5YzA4NmNi","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Paranoia. Once per day following an interaction with another creature (including other PCs) the DM can call on you to succeed on a Wisdom saving throw (DC 12) or you suspect that creature is secretly plotting against you. (3)","img":"https://static.thenounproject.com/png/2686179-200.png","resultId":null,"weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"collection":null,"rangeL":3,"rangeH":3},{"_id":"ZTcyMjRiZjcwZTc2","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Obsession. Choose a person or personal interest you are obsessed with. Once per day, when you are presented with an opportunity to interact with or learn more about the subject of your obsession the DM can call on you to succeed on a Wisdom saving throw (DC 14) or ignore everything else to obsess over the object of your fascination. (4)","img":"https://static.thenounproject.com/png/652020-200.png","resultId":null,"weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"collection":null,"rangeL":4,"rangeH":4},{"_id":"MWMxYjNhZmQwY2U2","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Addiction. Choose a behavior or substance you have used. Once per day, when you are presented with an opportunity to do the behavior or use the substance the DM can call on you to succeed on a Wisdom saving throw (DC 14) or ignore everything else to indulge in your vice. (5)","img":"https://static.thenounproject.com/png/859023-200.png","resultId":null,"weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"collection":null,"rangeL":5,"rangeH":5},{"_id":"Y2I3YWFkZDhhYjVm","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Odd Thinking. Once per day when you hear a rational explanation for an event or occurrence, your DM may call on you to succeed on a Wisdom saving throw (DC 12) or you reject the rational explanation for a conspiratorial or fantastical explanation. (6)","img":"https://static.thenounproject.com/png/1654953-200.png","resultId":null,"weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"collection":null,"rangeL":6,"rangeH":6},{"_id":"ZDk5MzY1NzhmNWVk","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Narcissism. When you take an action or series of action that doesnât directly benefit you, you must pass a Wisdom saving throw (DC 11) or you canât take that action / series of actions. If any self-sacrifice on your part would be required the DC of the saving throw is increased to 16. (7)","img":"https://static.thenounproject.com/png/2452310-200.png","resultId":null,"weight":1,"range":[7,7],"drawn":false,"collection":null,"rangeL":7,"rangeH":7},{"_id":"NGVmNjkyNTYxZDY2","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Delusional. When you gain this insanity the DM will tell you a belief that you have. No matter what evidence is presented to the contrary so long as you have this insanity you cannot be persuaded that this belief is not true. (8)","img":"https://static.thenounproject.com/png/3292671-200.png","resultId":null,"weight":1,"range":[8,8],"drawn":false,"collection":null,"rangeL":8,"rangeH":8},{"_id":"MmVjN2M5YTZjOWRk","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Pica. Once per day the DM can call on you to pass a Wisdom saving throw (DC 14) or immediately eat 